{
  "doc_id": "40323",
  "text": "Despite their perceived benefits, PILs are underutilised and poorly written [CITATION_1] . It is imperative that health professionals are aware of the accuracy, quality, and limitations of PILs that they use [CITATION_2] . PILs should also be based on the most current scientific evidence [CITATION_3] . The DIS-CERN instrument is a reliable and valid tool developed to allow both providers of health care and patients to assess the quality of written information relating to treatment choices [CITATION_4] .",
